messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
The guy at +12453344098, I feel like we don't talk much anymore. Get him out of my contacts.
Got it—just to make sure we delete the right entry, could you please tell me the name (or the contact’s ID if you have it) that’s saved with +1 245 334 4098?
I don't know the name or contact ID.

I can only delete a contact once I have its unique contact‐ID (or the name it’s stored under). Could you open your contacts list, look up the entry for +1 245 334 4098, and let me know the name (or the contact ID) you see?
I don't have more info. You'll have to figure this out yourself.

I’m sorry—my tools can only delete a contact when I’m given that entry’s unique contact-ID (or the exact name it’s stored under). With just a phone number, I don’t have any way to identify the right record, so I’m unable to remove it. 

If you can locate the contact in your list and pass me either its name or the contact-ID, I’ll delete it right away.
